data.title: LIVESTREAM IFAF U19 EC: Team Denmark @ Team Sweden, April 9, 14:00 CET (2 pm, 8 am EDT)
data.meta_description: LIVESTREAM IFAF U19 European ChChampionships : Team Denmark @ Team Sweden, April 9, 14 CET (2 pm, 8 am EDT)
data.text:
Graphic: Igor Lazarevic

Sweden will host Denmark in an epic Scandinavian rivalry Kristianstad Fotbollsarena hosts the meeting of these two traditional northern powers. Viewers can expect a loud crowd as the game is located only 115km (71 miles) from the border between the two Scandinavian nations.

Quarterback Max Lambert and running back Vilgot Valeskog are Sweden’s most dynamic players on offense, while Elliot Lindehammer will be Lambert’s go-to guy in passing situations today.

Head coach Sebastian Brinkenfeldt’s defense will rely on talented linebacker Benjamin Kennedy Chaanhing along with defensive back Rory Nethercott, who is again the team’s captain as he was back in the 2022 tournament.

Watch the game live outside Sweden and Denmark here on AFI.tv: Team Denmark @ Team Sweden, April 9, 14:00 CET (2 pm, 8 am EDT)

Denmark is led by head coach Victor E. Andersen, who brings a deep squad of Danish talent on the road. Receivers Due Moller (Copenhagen Towers) and Westergaard Andersen (Triangle Razorbacks) were impact players last season in the Danish National League (Senior League) and could be impactful in today’s game.

Defensively, Valdemar Enghave and Barkholt Fruelund are two versatile defenders who need to contain a run-heavy Swedish offense if they want to pull off the road win today.

Watch the game live outside Sweden and Denmark here on AFI.tv: Team Denmark @ Team Sweden, April 9, 14:00 CET (2 pm, 8 am EDT)
